article.headline: Louisiana Tech 73, Texas-San Antonio 71
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Kenyon McNeail scored 34 points, including the game-winning 3-pointer with 19 seconds left, as Louisiana Tech beat UTSA 73-71 Saturday night to complete a three-game road sweep through Texas. The Bulldogs (14-3, 5-0 Western Athletic), who have won six straight, beat Texas-Arlington and Texas State on the road last week before dispatching UTSA. Kannon Burrage had 29 points for UTSA (4-12, 0-6), which has lost six straight and 11 of its last 12. Jordan Sims added 16 points and Hyjii Thomas had 14. Louisiana Tech trailed 71-68 after Sims hit a 3-pointer with 1:26 remaining. Two free throws from McNeail made it a one-point game and Michale Kyser then blocked Burrage's shot on the other end to set up McNeail's game-winner. Thomas' 3-point attempt at the buzzer for UTSA was off the mark.
